text: Dr. Ray Peat was talking about how when taking Cascara it's best to put some on your tongue first and then swallow it, because the taste itself is essential for activating the digestive system. I think these androgenic bitter herbs Haidut mentioned like Tribulus might be similar.

Bryan Johnson type guys have given the topic of longevity a bad name by making it seem too vulgar. Rene Guenon talked about how in the East (like in Taoist texts) the concept of "longevity" has a connotation similar to "salvation of the soul" in Christianity. "The Great Triad".

That is not to say they didn't also aim for literal longevity in our sense of the word, but it was only secondary. E.g. Dr. Ray Peat pointed out Tai Chi methods work to increase CO2 retention, improve circulation, so when done in early morning hours may buffer nighttime stress.

I think Dr. Metchnikoff's observation that even though many old people generally tend to be somewhat selfish and self-centered, extremely old people (like in their 100s) are selfless and very interested in the lives of others. Extreme longevity predisposes to this personality.
